### Health: root
GET http://localhost:3001/ HTTP/1.1

### Health: users list (should return 200 if server is alive)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/users HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### Health: messages list (another simple GET endpoint)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/messages HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

### POST: register (sends OTP/chat) â€” useful to test POST handling
POST http://localhost:3001/api/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@example.com"
}

### POST: login (verify OTP/chat). Note: the server generates a random chat, so
### this will usually fail unless you set the correct `chat` value returned
### from the register step. Keep it for integration testing.
POST http://localhost:3001/api/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "chat": "1234"
}

